                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 7.047,
                                "byte_start": 105472,
                                "byte_stop": 133684,
                                "text": "The second case is an immigration case, an immigration that\u0027s called Nijhawan v. Holder."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 7.047,
                                "stop": 15.819,
                                "byte_start": 133684,
                                "byte_stop": 168793,
                                "text": "Immigration law permits the Government to deport an alien who is convicted of \u201caggravated felony\u201d."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 15.819,
                                "stop": 20.526,
                                "byte_start": 168793,
                                "byte_stop": 187601,
                                "text": "And there is a related statute, there\u0027s a whole lot of offenses that it calls aggravated felonies."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 20.526,
                                "stop": 22.159,
                                "byte_start": 187601,
                                "byte_stop": 194184,
                                "text": "It defines them."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 22.159,
                                "stop": 34.566,
                                "byte_start": 194184,
                                "byte_stop": 243816,
                                "text": "And one on that long list is \u201can offense that involves fraud or deceit in which the loss to the victims exceeds $10,000."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 34.566,
                                "stop": 47.844,
                                "byte_start": 243816,
                                "byte_stop": 296897,
                                "text": "The question here is, how does the immigration judge decide, whether a fraud offense of which an alien was previously convicted involved a loss to the victim exceeding $10,000?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 47.844,
                                "stop": 53.025,
                                "byte_start": 296897,
                                "byte_stop": 317586,
                                "text": "Does he just have to look at the fraud statute as it\u0027s described in the statute books?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 53.025,
                                "stop": 64.672,
                                "byte_start": 317586,
                                "byte_stop": 364189,
                                "text": "Let\u0027s see, for example, maybe there\u0027s a monetary threshold there, say, defining the crime as applying only where the loss is greater than $10,000 or $100,000 or greater than a million."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 64.672,
                                "stop": 74.042,
                                "byte_start": 364189,
                                "byte_stop": 401701,
                                "text": "And that threshold is convicted with guarantee that the fraud involved more than $10,000 because it\u0027s part of the definition."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 74.042,
                                "stop": 82.821,
                                "byte_start": 401701,
                                "byte_stop": 436809,
                                "text": "Or can the immigration judge also look to the proceedings in the fraud case itself to determine what actually happened?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 82.821,
                                "stop": 85.109,
                                "byte_start": 436809,
                                "byte_stop": 446004,
                                "text": "That matters in this case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 85.109,
                                "stop": 89.348,
                                "byte_start": 446004,
                                "byte_stop": 462932,
                                "text": "That\u0027s because the relevant fraud statute doesn\u0027t say anything about amounts."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 89.348,
                                "stop": 91.582,
                                "byte_start": 462932,
                                "byte_stop": 471813,
                                "text": "It doesn\u0027t have a threat to show."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 91.582,
                                "stop": 100.486,
                                "byte_start": 471813,
                                "byte_stop": 507444,
                                "text": "So, if we just read the statute, we can\u0027t tell whether the defendant defrauded the victim of $5 or $50,000."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 100.486,
                                "stop": 116.93,
                                "byte_start": 507444,
                                "byte_stop": 573273,
                                "text": "But we do know from the record in the particular case that the defendant stipulated its sentencing that the laws from his fraud exceeded a hundred million dollars and the sentencing judge ordered him to pay $683 million in restitution."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 116.93,
                                "stop": 121.223,
                                "byte_start": 573273,
                                "byte_stop": 590409,
                                "text": "We decide that the Immigration Judge can look beyond the statute."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 121.223,
                                "stop": 127.085,
                                "byte_start": 590409,
                                "byte_stop": 613815,
                                "text": "And in this case, we think the Immigration Judge was right to look at the sentencing record."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 127.085,
                                "stop": 142.574,
                                "byte_start": 613815,
                                "byte_stop": 675777,
                                "text": "There are so few fraud crimes defined in the statute books as containing monetary thresholds than to hold otherwise as the defendant wanted us to do would lead the immigration laws fraud provision without any coherent application."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 142.574,
                                "stop": 147.615,
                                "byte_start": 675777,
                                "byte_stop": 695944,
                                "text": "Moreover, we think there\u0027s sufficient safeguards for those threatened with deportation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 147.615,
                                "stop": 165.65,
                                "byte_start": 695944,
                                "byte_stop": 768146,
                                "text": "In the laws requirement that the Government at the deportation proceeding has to prove by clear and convincing evidence that that earlier fraud conviction did involve a loss of at least $10,000 or more and the Government must tie the laws to a specific count of conviction."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 165.65,
                                "stop": 168.382,
                                "byte_start": 768146,
                                "byte_stop": 779013,
                                "text": "We explained all this further in our opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 168.382,
                                "stop": 175.68,
                                "byte_start": 779013,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We affirmed the same conclusion reached by the Third Circuit and this decision is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
